reviews.text: This is a response to the reply. It has definitely been a mistake because I have not been at your place of business. From the other postings it seems that it is a legitimate comfortable place of relaxation. Hopefully in the near future I may be able to experience this business of accommodation and relaxation. Sorry for the mistake, unfortunately it was not my posting. I was actually trying to take the Stars off. But I would like to reiterate I do not hate this place for I have yet to try it out.
Great BNB . The owner was very nice and it was very clean and quiet . The food was above and beyond. It was a great weekend . Good location .  Highly recommend it.

Having the browning for my wedding weekend was one of the best and easiest decisions when planning my wedding. Liesl went out of her way to make it perfect and I could not be happier with how everything turned out. I could not say enough good things about this place. I felt at home and comfortable all weekend and it's just what I needed for that weekend.

My husband  and I stayed at The Historic Browning - Lee's Summit last week.  It is now a go to B and B for us.  The decor is clever, bright and cheerful.  The breakfast fresh and delicious.  The host delightful.  It is obvious that Liesl is focused and detailed oriented.  She does not miss a beat.

This beautifully restored and maintained historic inn is cozy, comfortable, and impeccably clean. The owner, Liesl, prepared a delicious breakfast. The location could not be better; just a short walk to local shops. Have fun all day and return for a good night's rest at the Browning.
The staff are the most helpful and kind to work with. With well kept grounds and the historical side of this place you would really be hard pressed to find a better cemetery.

This is a nice little cemetery. I enjoy it when cemeteries have the self guided walking tour information, and the literature given here was nice. There are several beautiful and unusual graves, especially that of WT Chrismas. The Youngers of the famous James-Younger gang are also buried here, and people often leave offerings to them even today. Overall it's small and may not look like much, but completely worth the visit.

Well maintained,
Good location,
Easy to Find
Interesting and fun location for a nice day activity!
Well attended to.

My husband and I walked in to this church knowing only that a priest who had formerly been in in charge at a church I had attended previously had taken over here. We were greeted by several welcoming folks and made to feel at home. Over the past several years, St. Paul's has become a part of our family; our son was baptized here and we've met some of our closest and dearest friends through the church. 

The programming has met all our needs, but we also see the leadership trying to offer alternatives for those who need something more or something "different." The church is growing and it's got a great vibe. Things are happening, and St. Paul's is instrumental in making them happen in the Clarence community.

St. Paul's is a wonderful church.  They're super welcoming to families, they've got great programs for children both young and old and they're a wonderful place for 20's and 30's: singles, couples and young families.  This is a growing place and it's got a great feel.

Come enjoy a step back in time. Visit the town set in the 1800s and soak in the history of the period. Visit all the homes and talk to the characters that host a house. They are full of knowledge and fun and entrain you.  Very kid friendly and school trips as well. They even have weddings set here. Bring your family and spend the afternoon.

What a great field trip destination, especially for kids that don't typically have a reason to venture out of their urban setting! Our class really enjoyed seeing the blacksmith in action and loved getting to touch a couple of "real live" farm animals. 
Make sure to check the forecast and dress accordingly (as some of our 2nd graders discovered the hard way). It's all outside, so consider bringing a jacket, sunscreen, bug spray, and a water bottle. Also, DEFINITELY wear some comfy walking shoes because there's lots of that. 
The only criticism I have is that some of the presentations were given very sloooooowly so the kids struggled a little bit with staying attentive and fidget free. Had the information had been more "rapid fire", I feel that there would have been more engagement and therefore, fewer instances of redirection. (Seriously, there was one presentation, that even as an adult, bored *me* to tears. 😴)
Over all though, we had a really great time and I'd highly recommend the experience!

Probably an awesome place when a festival is going on. Other than the person who took our money, we only saw a black smith.....no one else to talk to, nothing going on. Sooo spent money to walk around and see old buildings with no activity.  Also, I was told it was cheaper to come when there is a festival.
A fun family outing or just a good excuse to get some steps in.
Fun place to walk around and see history.

Check out the border wars and pat metheny exhibits
 Great. Highly recommended
What a neat place...packed with information and timeless treasures. If you grew up in LS, you'll be over the moon with memories. If you're new to LS, you'll love the history!
Very informative!! Town treasure for sure!
Wonderful artifacts!
Had a Terrific time on the Lake.
Love fishing this lake for most warm water species.  Walleye can be found here also.
The campgrounds are great, but as I said earlier, if you want to catch fish, this isn't the place.
Great nature trails.  The east side of the lake is great for morel hunting during the right time of year.  Numerous trails with some decent distance to hike.
The park is good
Fantastic outdoor location for many different activities!
Fun time throwing horse shoes and roasting a pig

This lake is good if you have a boat, but bank fishing is mediocre at best. 

If you do get the Jackson County pass to put a boat on the lake, you better be sure to be loaded up and leaving the park at sunset. Not at dark, not five minutes after sunset, you need to be rolling out at sunset. 

The park rangers here have little to no patience or understanding for people loading up and trying to get everything put away to leave. If you are still there in the park at sunset you are going to get a ticket.
Very busy during the day..got some awesome places there
only one problem, opens to late.

There is trash and garbage scattered all over the place and the restrooms are closed for the season! It is a peaceful place other than the total disrespect of others who leave garbage and don't know how to clean up after themselves! Didn't your momma teach you anything! Sadly to many people missed learning that basic life skill
Great place to take the litte nephew or nieces whip ate in from out of town
I launch my kayak here all the time. Very nice boat ramp for free. Also great place to bring my lab out to practice water retreives.
It's a nice Inner City Lake they keep up with it
Good fishing and bringing your family for picnics

My husband and i have been going since 2008 and we enjoy this beautiful park and its many garden themes, pathways, amazing lake and scenic views. There is always something happening there and new every time we go. On July 4th you must see the fireworks display! Take the family and a picnic dinner and stay for the orchestra and fireworks. A night you will not forget! I

We've been here both during the summer & winter. Each time, they have had the friendliest & most helpful customer service. We have never been disappointed in taking the 2 HR r/t drive to come visit.

The Festival of Lights was such a unique way to make what would normally be a dormant space in the winter, come alive.

This place maybe a little out of the way but well worth your time on the road. We are already making plans to see this garden in full bloom this spring. If it's anything like It was in the fall, them we are in for a treat. We're anxious to feast our eyes on the colors of spring as this place comes alive with the promise of new life. In addition the staff treated us with utmost respect, wanting us to have the best experience ever.  We highly recommend that you take time to take in this fantastic place of beauty, peace & tranquility.

Beautiful botanical gardens! Would highly recommend going between the months of March and October before the plants start withering but either way, it was a peaceful escape into nature! The chapel within the gardens is BEAUTIFUl and serene as well! The staff was helpful and extremely considerate, telling us to take our time despite their closing times. You can never go wrong with nature, but these botanical gardens go above and beyond with all the various species and varieties. Highly recommended :)

The staff was both welcoming and friendly. The facility was clean and well taken care of. The fireplace was my favorite part of our visit. The lights were a little underwhelming but they were pretty. It's a long walk for the light trail but there is a spot about halfway to stop and get warmed up, and pay 5 dollars for a cup of hot cider or cocoa if you're into that kinda price for that kind of thing.
We have taken our 4 children hiking here multiple times a year since the were old enough to walk. They all have a love for nature now. Just dont go after a rain, the best trails get very muddy.
I go here as often as I can. It has great hiking trails. Plenty of wildlife and good fishing at the lakes here.
This is one of our favorite fishing spots. Beautiful area, stocked lakes, easy access for those with physical limitations (like me)
Plenty of lakes to fish, so it's never too crowded. There is also a great walking trail that's stroller friendly.
James A. Reed is a beautiful park and I come here to do my homework all the time but I always catch trucks watching me from a distance or repeatedly passing by.
Great school
School

We had a great time at Got Art Gallery this past weekend.  A friend and I were co-hosting a bachelorette party and painting was one of the activities we wanted to do.  We picked Got Art for the location because we were able to walk from brunch to shopping to painting to whatever downtown nightlife we felt like.  I was so pleased with the custom painting that Teresa had created to fit our theme!  Our instructor was fun and easy going.  She was also very patient with our rambunctious group.  We had plenty of space for painting and also had an area for our snacks.  I was very pleased with the experience all around!
We had a great date night painting pineapples! Neither of us are artists, but we did a pretty good job! Lots of fun, and we'll be back!

My daughters Girl Scout troop took a painting class as I was walking around the studio looking at pictures my friend and I purchased some pictures we spent over 500 dollars two of the paintings where supposed to be shipped to my friend as he lives out of town.  He told us that they needed the pictures in the studio  for two more weeks we said ok that that when they were done they would call me to pick mine up and would ship him his. I never received a call to come pick it up, and they never sent my friend his pictures . We had to dispute the charge because somebody was not doing their job. This is frustrating as I already paid for these.... I will not be spending anymore of my money here in art and certainly will not recommend this place as the communication and lack of professionalism in this experience is extremely disrespectful and unprofessional.

We painted a cute snowman for an adult girl's birthday party. We were there for 2 hours, brought our own snacks and drinks and had a fabulous time. We each left with our own keepsake snowman painting (on canvas). Instruction was perfect for our novice level, fun music was playing in background ... an overall perfect experience.

We had a fun evening 6/10/16 with a party of seven ladies. Our instructor was great and patient.  (Ashley, I think) They have local artists' paintings & craft ware available for inspiration around the studio also.

Come enjoy a step back in time. Visit the town set in the 1800s and soak in the history of the period. Visit all the homes and talk to the characters that host a house. They are full of knowledge and fun and entrain you.  Very kid friendly and school trips as well. They even have weddings set here. Bring your family and spend the afternoon.

What a great field trip destination, especially for kids that don't typically have a reason to venture out of their urban setting! Our class really enjoyed seeing the blacksmith in action and loved getting to touch a couple of "real live" farm animals. 
Make sure to check the forecast and dress accordingly (as some of our 2nd graders discovered the hard way). It's all outside, so consider bringing a jacket, sunscreen, bug spray, and a water bottle. Also, DEFINITELY wear some comfy walking shoes because there's lots of that. 
The only criticism I have is that some of the presentations were given very sloooooowly so the kids struggled a little bit with staying attentive and fidget free. Had the information had been more "rapid fire", I feel that there would have been more engagement and therefore, fewer instances of redirection. (Seriously, there was one presentation, that even as an adult, bored *me* to tears. 😴)
Over all though, we had a really great time and I'd highly recommend the experience!

Probably an awesome place when a festival is going on. Other than the person who took our money, we only saw a black smith.....no one else to talk to, nothing going on. Sooo spent money to walk around and see old buildings with no activity.  Also, I was told it was cheaper to come when there is a festival.
A fun family outing or just a good excuse to get some steps in.
Fun place to walk around and see history.

When you want a delicious fresh made to order burger this is the place to go.  Great burgers ,fresh buns , and many delicious  toppings.  Food is  consistantly good and service is fast and friendly. I like when you order fries they don't skimp on the amount and always throw  extra into the bag.  Fries are cut fresh and delicious.  Clean restaurant with nice seating.  Free peanuts to munch on while you wait.  Food is delicious .  Love it.

This Five Guys was amazing. I was able to order online so I only waited a few minutes.  They gave me a free soft drink while I waited.  I received an amazing burger, plenty of perfect very hot fries.  Clean, quick and awesome service.

Always a good experience. Staff is pleasant (and they were even singing along to the music, which was fun) and the restaurant is always clean. Coke machine was out of quite a few flavor cartridges, but this was the first time that happened.

The food is good but I always thought it is expensive for what you get. 
We got 2 small cokes, small French fries, 1 bacon cheese burger (double patty) and 1 cheese burger (single) .... All for the bargain price of $27.30! Plus a wonderfully cozy atmosphere.
This place was always so clean & staff was so friendly. Anyone else notice the un-cleanliness or the attitudes between the pm manger & staff :(  we will not be returning!

Great food and staff. The place itself is small and can feel a bit cramped, but it seemed more cozy than cramped after a short time. The steak practically melted in my mouth! The seafood was fresh and delicious! The staff was nigh on perfect with their balance of being gone and their level of service. Love this place, worth the drive and time! Make a reservation and check it out!!

My first mother’s day was spent here. I enjoyed the setting so much. It’s situated on the Lake and was so beautiful to look at. I thought the views were incredible but the food was even more amazing. Every time I’ve gone I haven’t been disappointed.
Very good  food.  Parking and price not so much. Service was awesome. Our waiter Kyle was very attentive. Enjoyed the experience.

Very nice restaurant in the heart of a lake town.  Special NYE menu, steak and lobster mainly.  Pricey, but that's what you get with steak and lobster.  Reservations recommended.  Service was good, drinks arrived soon after ordering.  Dinner was a 4 course affair with appetizers, soup/salad, entree, and dessert included in the price.
Delicious steak, and cheesy potatoes! Celebrated my birthday there last week. Scallops for appetizer. I wasn't fond of the dressing on the pear and pecan salad. Beautiful sunset views.
We have taken our 4 children hiking here multiple times a year since the were old enough to walk. They all have a love for nature now. Just dont go after a rain, the best trails get very muddy.
I go here as often as I can. It has great hiking trails. Plenty of wildlife and good fishing at the lakes here.
This is one of our favorite fishing spots. Beautiful area, stocked lakes, easy access for those with physical limitations (like me)
Plenty of lakes to fish, so it's never too crowded. There is also a great walking trail that's stroller friendly.
